"Billboard device present" = "Billboard device present";
"A Billboard device is present on this port. That usually appears when an Alt Mode like DisplayPort was set up but didn't fully come up. Your display is below its best mode, so a re-plug, a different cable, or a different adapter may bring it up. Some docks show a Billboard device normally, so this isn't always a fault." = "A Billboard device is present on this port. That usually appears when an Alt Mode like DisplayPort was set up but didn't fully come up. Your display is below its best mode, so a re-plug, a different cable, or a different adapter may bring it up. Some docks show a Billboard device normally, so this isn't always a fault.";

/* Display dimension: compression at the link ceiling (issue #246). */
"Display may be using compression to reach its top mode" = "L'écran utilise peut-être la compression pour atteindre son mode maximal";
"Your %@ can run %@, which uncompressed would need about %@. This link is already running every lane at a high rate, carrying about %@ (%@). Many high-resolution displays use compression (DSC) to fit their top mode through a link like this, so the link rate alone can't tell whether you're already at your best mode. If the picture looks right, it most likely is." = "Votre %@ peut afficher %@, ce qui sans compression nécessiterait environ %@. Cette liaison utilise déjà toutes les voies à un débit élevé et transporte environ %@ (%@). De nombreux écrans haute résolution utilisent la compression (DSC) pour faire passer leur mode maximal par une liaison de ce type ; le débit de la liaison seul ne permet donc pas de savoir si vous êtes déjà dans votre meilleur mode. Si l'image semble correcte, c'est très probablement le cas.";

